# Artifact Discipline

Feedback weights **AI workflow and lifecycle artifacts** as much as working code. Update docs in the same session as the work they describe.

## When to Update What

| Activity | Update these files |
|----------|-------------------|
| Requirement clarification | `requirements-analysis.md`, `acceptance-criteria.md` |
| Architecture / design decision | `design-notes.md`, `data-model.md`, `ui-flow.md` |
| API implementation | `api-contract.md` (also see `api-contract-sync.mdc`) |
| Test plan or run | `test-strategy.md`, `test-results.md` |
| Bug investigation | `debugging-notes.md`, `ai-prompts/debugging.md` |
| Code review | `code-review-notes.md`, `review-fixes.md`, `ai-prompts/code-review.md` |
| Cursor session worth keeping | `ai-prompts/<phase>.md` via `capture-prompt-session` skill |
| Milestone complete | `implementation-plan.md` checkboxes, `pr-description.md` |

## Prompt History Format

Each entry in `ai-prompts/*.md`:

```markdown
## Session: <title>
**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD

### Prompt
<summary or text>

### AI Response Summary
<what was suggested>

### Accepted / Changed / Rejected
<what you did and why>
```

## Minimum Cadence

- After each major feature (auth, tickets CRUD, status, comments, export, search): one prompt capture + relevant artifact update
- Before submission: `reflection.md`, `final-ai-usage-summary.md`, `tool-workflow.md`, `candidate-info.md` complete

## Do Not

- Leave placeholder-only artifacts at submission
- Fabricate debugging or review notes — record real issues
- Dump entire chat logs — curate 10–15 representative sessions
